notes/conditions of use: Reference sites sampled over the geographic extent of 11.9.5 exhibited variation within some BioCondition attributes which lead to the development of two sets of benchmarks for this regional ecosystem. Areas in higher rainfall and/or higher soil fertility are represented by the tall or eastern form, while lower rainfall areas and /or lower soil fertility areas are represented by the short or western form. In general the eastern benchmark applies to the following subregions; Barakula (6[1]), Callide Creek Downs (19), Dulacca Downs (28), Eastern Darling Downs (31), Inglewood Sandstones (32), Moonie R.  Commoron Creek Floodout (33), Taroom Downs (25) and Weribone High (29). There will be variation within subregions, as some subregions span a large geographic range. In addition remnant 11.9.5, may occur to a minor extent in subregions not listed here, therefore, as a further guide in the choice of which benchmark document to use, practitioners can determine if remnant trees found in a local reference site are >20m, in which case they will choose the tall or eastern form, and where <20m the short or western form.

The western benchmark applies to the following subregions; Arcadia (20), Carnarvon Ranges (24), Claude River Downs (15), Dawson River Downs (21), Isaac-Comet Downs (11), Southern Downs (26), and Northern Bowen Basin (6). In addition remnant 11.9.5, may occur to a minor extent in subregions not listed here, therefore, as a further guide in the choice of which benchmark document to use, practitioners can determine if remnant trees found in a local reference site are >20m, in which case they will choose the tall or eastern form, and where <20m the short or western form.
